---
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="For Educators"
  description="Resources for teachers and workshop leaders to bring Lightning Piggy into the classroom"
>
  <div class="not-prose mb-8 p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-pink-light/30 to-yellow-light/30 rounded-2xl border border-pink/20">
    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Bring Bitcoin education to your classroom</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-600">
      Lightning Piggy combines STEM learning with financial literacy. Perfect for workshops,
      maker spaces, and Bitcoin meetups.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>Lightning Piggy works well in the following settings:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>A group build workshop.</li>
    <li>As part of an open-source project informal build area.</li>
    <li>A hands-on 'Character Design Challenge' for kids.</li>
    <li>A hands-on 'Piggy Build Challenge' for kids.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Group Build Workshop</h3>
  <p><a href="https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/1xdNpUF5waQ8qq2cIfzs03Brlgp1zpgLD4LHkzS0hOxs/embed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=3000">Embedded content</a></p>

  <h3>Open-Source Project Informal Build Area</h3>
  <p>Minimum Equipment List: A room/build area, table(s), chairs, laptop, wifi, power points, LightingPiggy boards and optional additional hardware as required.</p>

  <h3>Character Design Challenge</h3>
  <p>Students either choose or create their own character through drawing, painting, or coloring. Inspiration comes from Lightning Piggy's <a href="/about/origin-story">origin story</a>, about how he found freedom following an incredible journey down a rabbit hole, while on the run from an industrial pig farm.</p>
  <div class="not-prose mt-4 mb-8">
    <a href="/news/character-design-challenge" class="group block p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 hover:border-pink hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
      <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-pink transition-colors">Character Design Challenge →</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Choose a character and draw, paint and/or colour it.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h3>Piggy Build Challenge</h3>
  <p>Students design, build and decorate a piggy bank enclosure that can house the Lightning Piggy device using any materials they wish.</p>
  <div class="not-prose mt-4 mb-8">
    <a href="/news/build-challenge" class="group block p-6 bg-white rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 hover:border-pink hover:shadow-lg transition-all">
      <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 group-hover:text-pink transition-colors">Piggy Build Challenge →</h4>
      <p class="text-gray-600 mt-1">Design, build and decorate a piggy using any materials you wish.</p>
    </a>
  </div>

  <hr class="my-12 border-gray-200" />

  <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
  <p>
    Planning a workshop or educational event? We're here to help.
    Contact us at <a href="mailto:oink@lightningpiggy.com" class="text-pink">oink@lightningpiggy.com</a>
    for resources, bulk orders, or collaboration opportunities.
  </p>
</ContentLayout>
